RELEASE NOTES

Zeus is a powerful, fast and responsive, highly configurable
keyboard centric programmer's editor designed specifically for
the task of software development

Features

Some of the major features include:

Project/Workspace management
Syntax highlighting for C#, C/C++, Clipper, COBOL, D, Fortran
Go, HTML, Java, Pascal, Perl, Python, PHP, SQL etc
Easily configured to support any other programming language
Integrated class browser, code completion, code folding and
code navigation
Column mode cut, copy and paste
Keyboard macro record and playback with the recorded macro
being editable and re-runable
Fully scriptable using the Lua, Python, Java Script, Object
REXX, Ruby Script, VB Script or TCL languages
Full MSDN integration allows for fast keyword searching
Seamless FTP file editing includes support for SSH, SSL/TLS
secure FTP protocols
Brief, WordStar, Epsilon and Emacs keyboard emulation
Seamless Subversion integration allows SVN commands to be run
from within the IDE
Read what other users have to say about Zeus
and much more

All of these features along with a small footprint and fast file
loading makes Zeus the perfect programmer's editor

Listed below are just some of the features Zeus has to offer:

Syntax highlighting for C#, CC++, Clipper, COBOL, D, Fortran

Full-featured, highly configurable
The perfect CodeWright editor replacement
